There is yet one other slight indication of independent evidence possessed by Plutarch He gives us a detail relative to the siege oi Alesia which is not mentioned by Caesar, saying that the Romans, who were guarding the countervallation, were first apprised of the success of their countrymen against the relieving force by hearing the lamentatione of the Gauls in Alesia, when from their mountain-height they saw the spoils ol their countrymen being carried into the Roman camp.
